  "description": "A viscoplastic model in FLAC3D or 3DEC is characterized by a visco-elasto-plastic deviatoric behavior and an elasto-plastic volumetric behavior. The viscoelastic and viscoplastic strain-rate components are assumed to act in series. The viscoelastic constitutive law corresponds to a Burgers model (Kelvin cell in series with a Maxwell component), and the plastic constitutive law corresponds to a Mohr-Coulomb model . As a notation convention in this section, we use the symbols \\(S_{ij}\\) and \\(e_{ij}\\) to denote deviatoric stress and strain components: (1) \\[S_{ij}=\\sigma_{ij}-{\\sigma}_{0}\\delta_",
